Our Foundation

Mission, Vision &
Core Values

Established in 1994 under the banner of Sarvodaya Vidya Samsthe, and guided by the philosophy of Vidya Bharathi Karnataka, our school believes that genuine education shapes not only the intellect but also the character and values of every child we teach.

Est. 1994

Sarvodaya Vidya Mandira

Srinivasapura, Channarayapatna · Hassan, Karnataka

🎯

Our Mission

To deliver holistic, value-based English medium education that empowers children from all sections of society — equipping them with knowledge, practical skills, and moral integrity, and preparing them to lead with purpose, contribute meaningfully, and make their families and communities proud.

🌟

Our Vision

To be a centre of excellence where academic achievement goes hand in hand with cultural heritage, physical well-being, and ethical values — and where every student grows into a confident, compassionate, and capable individual.

These values are lived, not just listed.

Why Choose Us

What Sets Us
Apart

At Sarvodaya Vidya Mandira, a maximum of 30 students per class means every child is known by name, not just by rank. Our teachers follow up personally and parents are always kept in the loop. We combine disciplined academics with daily Yoga, regular assessments, sports, and cultural programmes — shaping children who are confident, grounded, and genuinely prepared for life.

💰

No Donation Policy

Quality education at a fully transparent, affordable fee structure. No hidden charges, no capitation fees — ever.

👥

Personalised Attention

No student has ever been lost in the crowd here. Our teachers know each child's strengths and struggles personally — and follow up without waiting to be asked.

🏆

Excellent SSLC Results

Our students achieve excellent results in the SSLC Board examination every year — a record of dedication we are proud of and fully committed to maintaining.

💻

Computer & Spoken English

Dedicated Computer Education and Spoken English classes integrated into the curriculum, preparing students for a modern and competitive world.

🧘

Yoga, Sports & Culture

Daily Yoga, sports, and rich cultural programmes develop the whole child — discipline, health, and confidence alongside academics.

🚌

Transport & Hostel

Safe, reliable school bus service and hostel accommodation available for students from across Channarayapatna taluk and surrounding villages.

Frequently Asked
Questions

Admissions are open every year from March to July. We encourage parents to enquire early as each class has a maximum of 30 students. Contact us on 9632490089 or email sarvodayaschool94@gmail.com to begin the process.
We offer a complete educational programme from Pre-KG (Nursery) through 10th Standard (SSLC Board). Each class has a maximum of 30 students to ensure that every child receives personalised attention.
The school follows the Karnataka State Board syllabus (KSEAB) from 1st Standard through 10th Standard (SSLC). The medium of instruction is English. The school is affiliated with Vidya Bharathi Karnataka and recognised by the Government of Karnataka.
There are no donation or capitation fees of any kind — ever. Sarvodaya Vidya Mandira follows a strict No Donation policy. Our fee structure is fully transparent and affordable. For current fee details, please call 9632490089 or email sarvodayaschool94@gmail.com and we'll be happy to share them.
Yes. We operate a safe, reliable school bus service covering Srinivasapura and the surrounding areas. Please call us for specific routes and timing details.
Yes, hostel accommodation is available for students who travel from distant areas. Please call us on 9632490089 or email sarvodayaschool94@gmail.com to learn about availability, facilities, and fee details.
Our students have consistently achieved strong results in the SSLC Board examination year after year — since our very first batch in 1994. This record of consistency and dedication is something we are fully committed to maintaining for every student we teach.
Students participate in Computer Education, Spoken English sessions, daily Yoga, sports, and a wide range of cultural programmes — all designed to develop the whole child, not just academic performance.
Yes. Sarvodaya Vidya Mandira is officially recognised by the Government of Karnataka and is affiliated with Vidya Bharathi Karnataka — one of the most respected educational organisations in the country.
